cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.DL 

This paper discusses the performance of state-of-the-art algorithms for automatic cognate detection, which is a task related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also evaluates the usefulness of automatic cognate detection for phylogenetic inference, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of automatic cognate detection for language phylogenies, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Linguistics) or cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
